ENVIRONMENT — Verifiable Accounting Arithmetic reference implementation (BSV-native)

TOOLCHAIN
  rust: 1.85.0 (pinned via rust-toolchain.toml)
  cargo: bundled with the pinned rustc
  target triples tested: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc, x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu, aarch64-apple-darwin

KEY DEPENDENCIES
  Versions below state the workspace minimum; exact resolved versions live in Cargo.lock.

  Hashing
    sha2             >= 0.10   (RustCrypto SHA-256; the BSV double-SHA256 primitive composes two SHA-256 invocations)

  Encoding / serialization
    serde, serde_json, ciborium, hex, hex-literal

  Errors / utilities
    thiserror, anyhow

  CLI
    clap (derive)

  Testing / benchmarks
    proptest, criterion

NETWORKS
  Default test/CI: offline only. All vectors are committed to /vectors.
  Optional live verification path against BSV mainnet / testnet headers is provided behind a
  feature flag, not enabled in CI.

HARDWARE FOR BENCHMARKS
  TBD - populated when the first benchmark run is captured in /bench. The benchmark harness
  reports median and IQR over many iterations on named hardware; no transactions-per-second
  figure is extrapolated.

REPRODUCIBILITY
  See docs/REPRODUCIBILITY.md for the exact commands to regenerate every value the paper cites.
